# MUTUAL FUND ANALYTICS PROJECT

## Final Capstone Report

### Prepared By

Ansh Jain

### University

Bennett University

### Program

B.Tech CSE (Data Science)

---

# 1. Executive Summary

The Mutual Fund Analytics Project is an end-to-end financial analytics solution developed to analyze mutual fund performance, investor behavior, risk measures, and market trends using Python-based technologies. The objective of this project is to transform raw mutual fund datasets into meaningful business insights through data engineering, exploratory data analysis, performance analytics, advanced risk analytics, and interactive dashboards.

The project includes multiple stages such as data ingestion, data cleaning, data validation, SQLite database creation, exploratory data analysis (EDA), performance analytics, advanced risk analysis, investor analytics, and dashboard creation.

Financial metrics such as CAGR, Sharpe Ratio, Sortino Ratio, Alpha, Beta, Maximum Drawdown, Value at Risk (VaR), and Conditional Value at Risk (CVaR) were calculated to evaluate mutual fund performance comprehensively.

Interactive dashboards were created using Plotly to visualize industry trends, investor behavior, SIP growth, and market movements.

Technologies Used:

• Python
• Pandas
• NumPy
• SQLite
• Plotly
• Matplotlib
• Seaborn
• Jupyter Notebook
• Git & GitHub

---

# 2. Project Objective

The primary objective of this project is to build a comprehensive Mutual Fund Analytics platform capable of analyzing mutual fund schemes, investor transactions, market benchmarks, and portfolio holdings.

The project aims to:

1. Build an ETL pipeline for mutual fund datasets.
2. Clean and validate financial datasets.
3. Perform exploratory data analysis.
4. Evaluate fund performance using financial metrics.
5. Analyze investor demographics and SIP behavior.
6. Develop interactive dashboards.
7. Build a recommendation system based on investor risk appetite.
8. Present findings in a professional report and dashboard.

---

# 3. Data Sources

The project uses the following datasets:

1. fund_master.csv
   Contains scheme information such as AMFI code, fund house, category, and plan.

2. nav_history.csv
   Contains historical NAV values for all schemes.

3. investor_transactions.csv
   Contains SIP, Lump Sum investments, and redemption transactions.

4. scheme_performance.csv
   Contains returns, AUM, expense ratios, and risk metrics.

5. category_inflows.csv
   Contains category-wise monthly inflows.

6. benchmark_indices.csv
   Contains NIFTY benchmark values used for Alpha and Beta calculations.

7. portfolio_holdings.csv
   Contains sector allocation and portfolio weights.

8. aum_by_fund_house.csv
   Contains AUM distribution across fund houses.

