# 5. Data Cleaning and Validation

The data cleaning phase involved:

• Handling missing values
• Standardizing transaction types
• Converting dates into datetime format
• Removing duplicate records
• Validating NAV and transaction values
• Ensuring referential integrity between datasets
• Creating processed datasets for analysis

SQLite was used to store cleaned datasets for efficient querying and data retrieval.

---

# 6. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Several visualizations were created to identify important trends.

Key Findings:

1. SIP inflows demonstrated a strong upward trend from 2022 to 2025.

2. SBI Mutual Fund emerged as the leading fund house in terms of Assets Under Management.

3. Large Cap schemes dominated investor preferences.

4. Tier-1 and T30 cities contributed the majority of investments.

5. Investor participation increased consistently across age groups.

6. Category-wise inflows showed strong growth in equity-oriented funds.

7. NAV values exhibited long-term growth across most schemes.

8. Folio count increased from 13.26 Crore to 26.12 Crore.

---

# 7. Performance Analytics

Several advanced financial metrics were calculated.

### CAGR

Compound Annual Growth Rate was used to measure annualized returns.

### Sharpe Ratio

Sharpe Ratio evaluated risk-adjusted returns by comparing excess returns with volatility.

### Sortino Ratio

Sortino Ratio considered downside risk and ignored positive volatility.

### Alpha

Alpha measured excess return over the benchmark.

### Beta

Beta measured sensitivity of fund returns to market returns.

### Maximum Drawdown

Maximum Drawdown quantified the largest decline from peak NAV.

### Value at Risk (VaR)

Historical VaR estimated the maximum expected loss at 95% confidence.

### Conditional VaR (CVaR)

CVaR measured the average loss beyond the VaR threshold.

---

# 8. Advanced Analytics

Advanced analytics included:

• Historical VaR for all schemes

• Conditional VaR (CVaR)

• Rolling 90-Day Sharpe Ratio

• Investor Cohort Analysis

• SIP Continuity Analysis

• Sector HHI Concentration Analysis

• Mutual Fund Recommendation System

The recommendation engine suggests funds based on investor risk appetite (Low, Moderate, High).

